s://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_janeway_ver01/data/sn87055779/00383349898/1930121901/0269.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87055779/1930-12-19/ed-1/?sp=13"], "batch": ["in_janeway_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/indiana/", "2/united states/indiana/saint joseph/", "3/united states/indiana/saint joseph/south bend/"], "contributor": ["indiana state library"], "date": "1930-12-19", "dates": ["1930-12-19"], "description": ["_ Always First SOUTH BEND NEWSTIMES T Always Fair DAT AND NIGHT flILLT LRASED WIRE TELEGRAPHIC SERVICE SOUTH BEND INDIANA FRIDAY DECEMBER 19 1930 PART TWO POUCE DRAG RIVER FOR BODY OF MISSING LDMBER COMPANY OFFICIAL _ Leslies Proposed Sales Tax Heartily Scored at Meeting Held in Chamber of Commerce LATZ IN ADDRESS CLAIMS MEASURE HURTS POOR MAN Plan Would Retard Sales and Hurt Merchant Speaker Says The recommendation of Governor Leslies tax commission for the enactment of a one per cent tax on the sale of all merchandise in the state of Indiana came under heavy fire at meeting of merchants and other members of the Chamber of Commerce Thursday E Irving Latz Fort Wayne mer chant addressed the gathering at tacking the proposed tax as funda mentally unsound State Senator Chester A Perkins and State Representativeselect John B Kuespert Charles J Allardt and Francis B Salata were present at the meeting and listened to the argu ments Might Reduce Purchasing A direct charge on purchases of merchandise such as will be pro posed at the next meeting of the legislature would be bound to reduce the purchasing power of the con sumer Mr Latz said It would definitely"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-05-19T00:56:29.168Z", "group": ["ndnp/in", "indiana-state-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87055779/1930-12-19/ed-1/?sp=13", "image_url":